name: fdm_a350_dual
machine_start_gcode:
; Model: Snapmaker A350 Dual ({nozzle_diameter[0]}/{nozzle_diameter[1]})
; Update: 20231019
; Maintained by https://github.com/macdylan/3dp-configs
; Printer : [printer_preset]
; Profile : [print_preset]
; Plate   : [plate_name]
; --- initial_extruder: [initial_extruder]
; --- has_wipe_tower: [has_wipe_tower]
; --- total_toolchanges: [total_toolchanges]
; --- T0: {is_extruder_used[0]}
; --- T1: {is_extruder_used[1]}

T[initial_extruder]

M140 S{first_layer_bed_temperature[initial_extruder]}

; you can clean the nozzle
{if is_extruder_used[0]}M104 T0 S165{endif}
{if is_extruder_used[1]}M104 T1 S165{endif}
M204 S100
G28
G0 Z193 F960.0
G0 Y175.0 F3420.0
G0 X160.0

M190 R{first_layer_bed_temperature[initial_extruder]}

G28
G0 X0
G0 Z0.2 F960.0
G0 Y0 F3420.0
G0 X320
G0 Y350
G0 X0
G0 Y0

M83

{if is_extruder_used[0]}M104 T0 S{max(250, min(290, nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[0] + 15))}{endif}
{if is_extruder_used[1]}M104 T1 S{max(250, min(290, nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[1] + 15))}{endif}

{if is_extruder_used[0] and initial_extruder != 0}
  T0
G0 Z20 F960.0
G0 X{if 0 == 0}-10{else}330{endif} F3420.0
G0 Y0

M109 S{max(250, min(290, nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[0] + 15))} C2 W1; common flush temp
G0 E45 F80.0

M106 S{min(255, (fan_max_speed[0] + 10) * 2.55)}
M104 S{nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[0] + 5}

G0 E45 F200

G0 E-0.5 F200
M107

G0 Z0.1 F960.0
G0 X{if 0 == 0}10{else}310{endif} F3420.0
G0 X{if 0 == 0}-10{else}330{endif}

G0 Z1.0 F960.0

M109 S{nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[0]} C3 W1
G1 X{if 0 == 0}150.0{else}170.0{endif} F3420.0
G1 Z0.3 F960.0
G1 E4 F200
G1 X{if 0 == 0}0{else}320{endif} E9.35442 F3420.0
G1 Y11 E0.68599
G1 X{if 0 == 0}0.5{else}319.5{endif}
G1 E0.4
G1 Y0.8 E0.6361
G1 X{if 0 == 0}9.5{else}310.5{endif} E0.59245
G1 E-0.5 F200
G92 E0

  M104 S{temperature_vitrification[0]}
{endif}
{if is_extruder_used[1] and initial_extruder != 1}
  T1
G0 Z20 F960.0
G0 X{if 1 == 0}-10{else}330{endif} F3420.0
G0 Y0

M109 S{max(250, min(290, nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[1] + 15))} C2 W1; common flush temp
G0 E45 F80.0

M106 S{min(255, (fan_max_speed[1] + 10) * 2.55)}
M104 S{nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[1] + 5}

G0 E45 F200

G0 E-0.5 F200
M107

G0 Z0.1 F960.0
G0 X{if 1 == 0}10{else}310{endif} F3420.0
G0 X{if 1 == 0}-10{else}330{endif}

G0 Z1.0 F960.0

M109 S{nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[1]} C3 W1
G1 X{if 1 == 0}150.0{else}170.0{endif} F3420.0
G1 Z0.3 F960.0
G1 E4 F200
G1 X{if 1 == 0}0{else}320{endif} E9.35442 F3420.0
G1 Y11 E0.68599
G1 X{if 1 == 0}0.5{else}319.5{endif}
G1 E0.4
G1 Y0.8 E0.6361
G1 X{if 1 == 0}9.5{else}310.5{endif} E0.59245
G1 E-0.5 F200
G92 E0

  M104 S{temperature_vitrification[1]}
{endif}

T[initial_extruder]
G0 Z20 F960.0
G0 X{if initial_extruder == 0}-10{else}330{endif} F3420.0
G0 Y0

M109 S{max(250, min(290, nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[initial_extruder] + 15))} C2 W1; common flush temp
G0 E45 F80.0

M106 S{min(255, (fan_max_speed[initial_extruder] + 10) * 2.55)}
M104 S{nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[initial_extruder] + 5}

G0 E45 F200

G0 E-0.5 F200
M107

G0 Z0.1 F960.0
G0 X{if initial_extruder == 0}10{else}310{endif} F3420.0
G0 X{if initial_extruder == 0}-10{else}330{endif}

G0 Z1.0 F960.0

M109 S{nozzle_temperature_initial_layer[initial_extruder]} C3 W1
G1 X{if initial_extruder == 0}150.0{else}170.0{endif} F3420.0
G1 Z0.3 F960.0
G1 E4 F200
G1 X{if initial_extruder == 0}0{else}320{endif} E9.35442 F3420.0
G1 Y11 E0.68599
G1 X{if initial_extruder == 0}0.5{else}319.5{endif}
G1 E0.4
G1 Y0.8 E0.6361
G1 X{if initial_extruder == 0}9.5{else}310.5{endif} E0.59245
G1 E-0.5 F200
G92 E0

; ready [plate_name]
machine_end_gcode:
G92 E0

G0 Z{max_layer_z + 0.5} F600
; retract the filament to make it easier to replace
G0 E-35 F200
G28

    {if is_extruder_used[0]}M104 T0 S0{endif}
    {if is_extruder_used[1]}M104 T1 S0{endif}
M140 S0
M107
M220 S100
M84

;
; DON'T REMOVE these lines if you're using the smfix (https://github.com/macdylan/SMFix)
; min_x = [first_layer_print_min_0]
; min_y = [first_layer_print_min_1]
; max_x = [first_layer_print_max_0]
; max_y = [first_layer_print_max_1]
; max_z = [max_layer_z]
; total_layer_number = [layer_num]
;
